
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `namecheck` baraye baresi kardan esm-haye karbari (usernames) dar platform-haye mokhtalef online (mesle social media, domain-ha va gheireh) be kar miravad. Ba estefade az in dastoor, shoma mitavanid be asani bebinid aya yek esm-e khas dar chand site-e mokhtalef gheire ghabele dastras ast ya na.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `namecheck username`  -->  🔍 Baresi esm-e karbari dar hameye platform-haye pishfarz.
    🔹 `namecheck --only <platform1,platform2,...> username`  -->  🎯 Baresi esm-e karbari faghat dar platform-haye entekhab shode.
    🔹 `namecheck --available username`  -->  ✅ Faghat platform-hayei ra namayesh midahad ke esm-e karbari dar anha dastras ast.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ namecheck javad123

    🔹 Baresi esm-e karbari "javad123" dar hameye platform-haye pishfarz.

    $ namecheck --only twitter,facebook,instagram javad123

    🔹 Baresi esm-e karbari "javad123" faghat dar Twitter, Facebook, va Instagram.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ namecheck --available javad123

    🔹 Namayesh platform-hayei ke esm-e karbari "javad123" dar anha hanooz gerefte nashodeh va dastras ast. Agar hich natijeyi namayesh dade nashavad, yani esm-e karbari dar hich platform-e dastrasi dastras nist.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `namecheck` command is used to check the availability of usernames across various online platforms (such as social media, domains, etc.).  Using this command, you can easily see if a specific username is unavailable on different sites.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `namecheck username`  -->  🔍 Check the username on all default platforms.
    🔹 `namecheck --only <platform1,platform2,...> username`  -->  🎯 Check the username only on the specified platforms.
    🔹 `namecheck --available username`  -->  ✅ Show only platforms where the username is available.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ namecheck javad123

    🔹 Check the username "javad123" on all default platforms.

    $ namecheck --only twitter,facebook,instagram javad123

    🔹 Check the username "javad123" only on Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ namecheck --available javad123

    🔹 Displays the platforms where the username "javad123" is still available. If no output is shown, it means the username is not available on any supported platform.
